trans-unit.source: The Get User’s manager operation gets the user’s manager.
trans-unit.target: The Get User’s manager operation gets the user’s manager.

trans-unit.source: This can be a contact or another user.
trans-unit.target: This can be a contact or another user.

trans-unit.source: The request may be constructed as follows.
trans-unit.target: The request may be constructed as follows.

trans-unit.source: Replace <parameterReference>mytenantdomain</parameterReference> with the domain of your Azure Active Directory tenant, such as <parameterReference>contoso.onmicrosoft.com</parameterReference>.
trans-unit.target: Replace <parameterReference>mytenantdomain</parameterReference> with the domain of your Azure Active Directory tenant, such as <parameterReference>contoso.onmicrosoft.com</parameterReference>.

trans-unit.source: The <parameterReference>api-version</parameterReference> query string parameter is required.
trans-unit.target: The <parameterReference>api-version</parameterReference> query string parameter is required.

trans-unit.source: If “$links” is included in the URI, then the response will contain only links to the relevant directory objects.
trans-unit.target: If “$links” is included in the URI, then the response will contain only links to the relevant directory objects.

trans-unit.source: If “$links” is omitted from the URI, the objects themselves are returned.
trans-unit.target: If “$links” is omitted from the URI, the objects themselves are returned.

trans-unit.source: Either <embeddedLabel>objectId</embeddedLabel> or <embeddedLabel>userPrincipalName</embeddedLabel> may be used to specify the target user.
trans-unit.target: Either <embeddedLabel>objectId</embeddedLabel> or <embeddedLabel>userPrincipalName</embeddedLabel> may be used to specify the target user.

trans-unit.source: To retrieve the manager for a contact, specify “contacts” as the resource set.
trans-unit.target: To retrieve the manager for a contact, specify “contacts” as the resource set.

trans-unit.source: You can also specify “directoryObjects” as the resource set in the request URI; for example, https://graph.windows.net/contoso.onmicrosoft.com/directoryObjects/ea59e4d3-a7a1-4b5b-b65f-a25fcc0c0f99/manager?api-version=2013-04-05.
trans-unit.target: You can also specify “directoryObjects” as the resource set in the request URI; for example, https://graph.windows.net/contoso.onmicrosoft.com/directoryObjects/ea59e4d3-a7a1-4b5b-b65f-a25fcc0c0f99/manager?api-version=2013-04-05.
